    { q: "What is the significance of the 'volatile' keyword when reading hardware status registers inside a while loop waiting for a flag to clear?", opts: ["It prevents the compiler from caching the register value in a CPU register and optimizing away repeated memory reads", "It ensures atomic access across multiple CPU cores", "It forces the CPU to execute at maximum clock speed", "It automatically debounces the register reading"], correctAnswer: "It prevents the compiler from caching the register value in a CPU register and optimizing away repeated memory reads" }
